Port Vale face an anxious wait over the fitness of Nathan Smith after the 20-year-old was forced off during the 3-2 defeat at Scunthorpe with a suspected hamstring injury. 
 
Smith had to be substituted on 54 minutes yesterday, ending his record of playing every minute of every game in all 34 of Vale&apos;s matches in all competitions this season. 
 

 
Port Vale lost 3-2 at Scunthorpe 
 
The youngster was replaced by Kjell Knops who was signed to play in central defence in the summer, but has been used at left back because Smith and Remie Streete have been so impressive in the middle. 
 
