Knops had lost his place in the starting line up to left back Scott Tanser who made his Vale debut after signing from Rochdale on Friday on a deal until the end of the season. 
 
Vale&apos;s battling performance wasn&apos;t quite enough against a Scunthorpe side who moved to the top of League One with the win. 
 
Tyler Walker fired Vale in front on 38 minutes but Josh Morris levelled four minutes into the second half after Streete was judged to have fouled former Vale striker Craig Davies. 
 
JJ Hooper restored Vale&apos;s lead on 59 minutes but goals from Ivan Toney, on 62, and Tom Hopper, on 71 minutes, condemned Vale to a 3-2 defeat which sends them down three places to 18 th . 
 
